In [31]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
car_crashes = sns.load_dataset("car_crashes")
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(x='abbrev', y='total', data=car_crashes, palette='coolwarm')
plt.xlabel('Abbreviation')
plt.ylabel('Total Car Crashes')
plt.title('Total Car Crashes by State Abbreviation')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.show()

Inference: By the graph we can observe that , the total number of crashes in each state ,the highest number of crashes are observed in three states i.e..ND,SC,WV.
